<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 2255/96 of 19 November 1996 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2255/96, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile 19. november 1996 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 75 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 75, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of the Treaty (3), </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189c s&auml;testatud korras (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas point 1 of Article 3 of Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 (4) provides that the Member States may grant aid designed to facilitate the development of more economic transport systems and technologies for the Community in general, and the development of combined transport; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 (4) artikli 3 punktiga 1 n&auml;hakse ette, et liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad anda toetusi, et h&otilde;lbustada kogu &uuml;hendusele soodsamate transpordis&uuml;steemide ja -tehnoloogiate ning kombineeritud transpordi arendamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the costs of loading and unloading form a significant part of the total cost of transport by inland waterway; whereas it is essential to the development of inland waterway transport for major investments to be made to render loading and unloading installations and equipment for interland waterway terminals more efficient and better suited to the current logistical requirements; whereas, to this end, it is important that aid granted by the Member States or through State resources can be made available to the undertakings concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> lastimis- ja lossimiskulud moodustavad olulise osa siseveetranspordi kogukuludest; siseveetranspordi arendamiseks on vaja teha suuri investeeringuid, et muuta lastimis- ja lossimisrajatised ja siseveetranspordi terminalide seadmed t&otilde;husamaks ning kohandada neid vastavalt kehtivatele logistikan&otilde;uetele; seep&auml;rast on oluline, et liikmesriikide poolt v&otilde;i riigi varudest antavad toetused oleksid asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele k&auml;ttesaadavad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas harmonized conditions should be laid down for the granting of this aid for the development of inland waterway transport and whereas the impact of the aid must be assessed at regular intervals; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb s&auml;testada siseveetranspordi arendamiseks toetuste andmise &uuml;htlustatud tingimused ning hinnata toetuste m&otilde;ju korrap&auml;raste ajavahemike j&auml;rel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this aid must be granted for a sufficiently long period for the said investment to have the time to win over the market and bring new traffic to inland waterways and whereas the Council should decide on subsequent arrangements, </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused toetused peavad olema piisavalt pikaajalised, et investeeringute tulemusel suudetaks leida turul oma tarbijaskond ja laiendada liiklust siseveeteedel; n&otilde;ukogu peab tegema otsuse edaspidi kohaldatava korra kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Sole Article </inglise>
<eesti> Ainus artikkel </eesti>
<inglise> The following shall be added to point 1 of Article 3 of Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 artikli 3 punktile 1 lisatakse j&auml;rgnev: </eesti>
<inglise> '(f) up to 31 December 1999, where aid is granted on a temporary basis and is designed to facilitate the development of inland waterway transport, such aid having to be either: </inglise>
<eesti> "(f) kuni 31. detsembrini 1999 juhul, kui toetusi antakse ajutiselt ja need on m&otilde;eldud siseveetranspordi arendamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks; toetusi antakse &uuml;hes j&auml;rgnevas vormis: </eesti>
<inglise> - investments in the infrastructure of inland waterway terminals; or </inglise>
<eesti> - siseveetranspordi terminalide infrastruktuuri tehtavad investeeringud v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - investments in the fixed and mobile equipment needed for loading and unloading. </inglise>
<eesti> - investeeringud lastimiseks ja lossimiseks vajalikesse p&uuml;si- ja liikuvseadmetesse. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid granted may not exceed 50 % of the total amount of investment. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetused ei tohi &uuml;letada 50% investeeringute kogumahust. </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of the aid shall be to develop new or additional transport tonnage on the inland waterway. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetuste eesm&auml;rk on arendada siseveeteedel uut v&otilde;i lisaveotonnaa&zcaron;i. </eesti>
<inglise> The beneficiaries must comply with the detailed arrangements laid down by the Member State concerned and shall be responsible for the actual carrying out of the investment. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetuste saajad peavad t&auml;itma asjaomaste liikmesriikide s&auml;testatud tingimusi ja vastutama tegeliku investeerimise eest. </eesti>
<inglise> Every two years the Commission shall submit to the European Parliament and the Council a progress report on the implementation of the measures, stating in particular the purpose of the aid, the amount and its impact on inland waterway transport. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga kahe aasta j&auml;rel esitab komisjon Euroopa Parlamendile ja n&otilde;ukogule meetmete rakendamise kohta arengu aruande, mis sisaldab eelk&otilde;ige toetuste eesm&auml;rki ja suurust ning nende m&otilde;ju siseveetranspordile. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall provide the Commission with the information needed to draw up this report. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile selle aruande koostamiseks vajaliku teabe. </eesti>
<inglise> No later than 31 July 1999 the Council shall decide, on a proposal from the Commission and under the conditions set out in the Treaty, on subsequent arrangements or, where appropriate, on the conditions for terminating the arrangements. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu teeb komisjoni ettepanekul ja asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud tingimustel hiljemalt 31. juulil 1999 otsuse edaspidi kohaldatava korra kohta v&otilde;i vajaduse korral korra kohaldamise l&otilde;petamise kohta." </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 19 November 1996. </inglise>
